{
  "stem": "7506.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was of aware of the fact-- as I have been many different occasions throughout my life-- that it's not such a great thing to be Jewish, that it's not such a-- maybe such a mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As all my life-- more so when I never came to the United States-- before I came to the United States, I've always been rather reluctant to say I'm Jewish because my feelings about it is-- because of being Jewish, terrible things have happened to me and my family.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm convinced today, cynical though it may seem, that there is almost no less anti-Semitism now as what was then.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I fear it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I fear it not for me, obviously.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I fear it for my fellow Jews all over the world, including in Israel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I fear it also because of, I suppose, the old kind of thought of what happens to the Jews will eventually happen to others, which indeed is how things happen.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That picture was taken by the part of the army-- British Army-- that liberated Belsen, that came into the barrack.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took the picture of my sister in her bunk bed at time of the liberation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that picture eventually wound up in the Imperial War Museum in London in England.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we got a copy of that picture from the Imperial War Museum in England.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was taken either on the liberation day on the 15th of April, or it was taken very soon thereafter, because the date of my sister's death is the 24th of April, 1945, which is exactly nine days after the liberation that she died in the hospital outside Bergen.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "12.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sister was 12.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah, Hetty.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That she took you to her grave site.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
